  <notes>
    **Additive-only is non-negotiable**. The existing entity is in production and existing chat surfaces depend on its current shape. If you find yourself wanting to rename a field or change a type â€” STOP. Investigate whether you can add a new field with the desired shape and let the old field remain unused (Phase 5 can migrate consumers).

    The `isDefaultLanding = true` constraint (exactly one row per tenant) is operationally enforced (BFF layer + seed data discipline). Dataverse doesn't support partial-unique constraints natively. If a future change wants to enforce this at the database layer, see `docs/data-model/` for the approach.

    The placeholder seed row in step 8 will have `defaultPlaybookId = null` until task 052 seeds the default "Spaarke Assistant â€” General" playbook. That's fine â€” the `launch-resolver.ts` (task 050) will handle null playbook IDs gracefully (fall back to a hardcoded default in the BFF or surface an error message).

    If `tenantId` is already present on the entity, leave it alone. If not, add it as a required field â€” but verify there are no existing rows in production first (an existing row without tenantId would fail the required-field constraint).

    Solution segmentation: if the entity is in solution X and we want the new fields in solution Y (SpaarkeActionEngine), Dataverse solution segmentation lets us layer additions. Verify support before assuming.

    Do NOT register new plugins on this entity (ADR-002). The launch-resolver and routing logic lives in client + BFF, not in plugins.
  </notes>

